com.samsung.android.sdk.healthdata

Interface HealthConstants.Exercise

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HealthConstants.Common, HealthConstants.SessionMeasurement
    Enclosing class:
    HealthConstants

    public static interface HealthConstants.Exercise
extends HealthConstants.SessionMeasurement
    This interface defines constants for exercise information data of user.

    LIVE_DATA and LOCATION_DATA

    LIVE_DATA and LOCATION_DATA of this interface need to be converted to compressed JSON when you add exercise data to the health data store. Refer to the following example. 

     import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;
 import java.io.IOException;
 import java.util.ArrayList;
 import java.util.zip.GZIPOutputStream;
 import com.google.gson.Gson;

 import com.samsung.android.sdk.healthdata.*;

 public class ExerciseExample {

     public class LiveData {
         long start_time = 0L;
         float heart_rate = 0.f;
         float cadence = 0.f;
         float count = 0.f;
         float power = 0.f;
         float speed = 0.f;
     }

     public byte[] getCompressedJson(ArrayList<LiveData> liveData) throws IOException {
         // translate data class to JSON string
         Gson gson = new Gson();
         String jsonStr = gson.toJson(liveData);

         // compress JSON
         ByteArrayOutputStream bos = new ByteArrayOutputStream(jsonStr.length());
         GZIPOutputStream gos = new GZIPOutputStream(bos);
         gos.write(jsonStr.getBytes());
         gos.close();
         byte[] zip = bos.toByteArray();
         bos.close();

         return zip;
     }
 }

    LIVE_DATA and LOCATION_DATA can be check from compressed JSON as the following example. 

     import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;
 import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;
 import java.io.IOException;
 import java.util.ArrayList;
 import java.util.List;
 import java.util.zip.GZIPInputStream;
 import java.util.zip.GZIPOutputStream;
 import com.google.gson.Gson;
 import com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException;
 import com.google.gson.reflect.TypeToken;

 import com.samsung.android.sdk.healthdata.*;

 public class ExerciseExample {

     public class LiveData {
         long start_time = 0L;
         float heart_rate = 0.f;
         float cadence = 0.f;
         float count = 0.f;
         float power = 0.f;
         float speed = 0.f;
     }

     public ArrayList<LiveData>getLiveData(byte[] zip) throws IOException, JsonSyntaxException {
         // decompress ZIP
         final int BUFFER_SIZE = 1024*1000;
         ByteArrayInputStream bis = new ByteArrayInputStream(zip);
         GZIPInputStream gis = new GZIPInputStream(bis, BUFFER_SIZE);
         StringBuilder jsonBuilder = new StringBuilder();
         byte[] data = new byte[BUFFER_SIZE];
         int bytesRead;
         while ((bytesRead = gis.read(data)) != -1) {
             jsonBuilder.append(new String(data, 0, bytesRead));
         }
         gis.close();
         bis.close();

         // translate JSON string to data class
         ArrayList<LiveData> liveData = new ArrayList<LiveData>();
         Gson gson = new Gson();
         liveData = gson.fromJson(jsonBuilder.toString(), new TypeToken<List<LiveData>>() {}.getType());
         return liveData;
     }
 }

      • EXERCISE_CUSTOM_TYPE

        static final String EXERCISE_CUSTOM_TYPE
        Custom exercise type. Define its value as FQDN, e.g. "com.yourcompany.exercise.type.exercise_name".

        This property has to be used only when you cannot find a required exercise type in predefined types. If this custom type is used, set the value of EXERCISE_TYPE as 0. Your custom health data is inserted to the health data store but it is not shown in S Health.

        • Optional
        • Type: String
        • Value length: 1 ~ 255

      • LIVE_DATA

        static final String LIVE_DATA
        Live data (e.g. heart rate, speed, power, and so on) during exercise which is JSON formatted and ZIP compressed.

        • Optional
        • Type: byte[]
        • Maximum data size: 1000 KB

        Live data is retrieved from compressed JSON. JSON keys for this property are the followings.

        JSON key Type Mandatory
        "start_time" long Yes
        "heart_rate" float No
        "cadence" float No
        "count" int No
        "power" float No
        "speed" float No

        The following example shows the JSON format for LIVE_DATA. 

           {
     "start_time":1422457096536,
     "heart_rate":147.48181,
     "cadence":95.84712,
     "count":83,
     "power":99.50436,
     "speed":11.061617
 }

        Its use cases are as below.

        • Converting to compressed JSON
        • Getting live data from compressed JSON

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • LOCATION_DATA

        static final String LOCATION_DATA
        Location (trajectory) data during exercise which is JSON formatted and ZIP compressed.

        • Optional
        • Type: byte[]
        • Maximum data size: 1000 KB

        Location data is retrieved from compressed JSON. JSON keys for this property are the followings.

        JSON key Type Mandatory
        "start_time" long Yes
        "latitude" float No
        "longitude" float No
        "altitude" float No
        "accuracy" float No

        The following example shows the JSON format for LOCATION_DATA 

           {
     "start_time":1422457096536,
     "latitude":2.7413864,
     "longitude":60.37224,
     "altitude":39.0,
     "accuracy":0.0
 }

        Its use cases are as below.

        • Converting to compressed JSON
        • Getting live data from compressed JSON
